trans-unit.source: Represents a 2-D geometric shape defined by the combination of two <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Geometry"></xref> objects.
trans-unit.target: Representerer en geometrisk figur 2-D er definert av kombinasjonen av to <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Geometry"> </xref> objekter.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry.GeometryCombineMode%2A> property specifies how the two geometries will be combined.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry.GeometryCombineMode%2A>egenskapen angir hvordan to geometri skal kombineres.</xref:System.Windows.Media.CombinedGeometry.GeometryCombineMode%2A>

trans-unit.source: Note that CombinedGeometry combines the area specified by two geometries, so geometries that do not have area (such as <xref:System.Windows.Media.LineGeometry>) disappear when combined.
trans-unit.target: Obs CombinedGeometry kombinerer området som er angitt av to geometri, så geometri som ikke har området (eksempel <xref:System.Windows.Media.LineGeometry>) forsvinner når kombineres.</xref:System.Windows.Media.LineGeometry>

trans-unit.source: Geometries can be combined in several ways: using a <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup>, a CombinedGeometry, or the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A> method of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> class.
trans-unit.target: Du kan kombinere geometri på flere måter: med en <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup>, en CombinedGeometry eller <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A>-metoden til <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>klasse.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup>

trans-unit.source: - A <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup> creates a composite geometry from one or more <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> objects.
trans-unit.target: -A <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup>oppretter en sammensatt geometri fra én eller flere <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>objekter.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> </xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup>

trans-unit.source: - A CombinedGeometry uses a specified boolean operation to combine the area described by two <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> objects.
trans-unit.target: – En CombinedGeometry bruker en angitt boolsk operasjon til å kombinere diagramområdet som er beskrevet av to <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>objekter.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>

trans-unit.source: - The static <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A> method of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> class behaves in exactly the same manner as the CombinedGeometry object.
trans-unit.target: -Statiske <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A>metoden for den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry>klassen håndterer på samme måte som CombinedGeometry-objekt.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Geometry.Combine%2A>

trans-unit.source: Careful thought should be involved when using a CombinedGeometry to perform a union as it can be very CPU-expensive.
trans-unit.target: Forsiktig tanke må være involvert når du bruker en CombinedGeometry til å utføre en union som det kan være svært CPU-kostbar.

trans-unit.source: In most cases, a <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup> or <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry.AddGeometry%2A> will work better.
trans-unit.target: I de fleste tilfeller en <xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup>eller <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry.AddGeometry%2A>fungerer bedre.</xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry.AddGeometry%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.GeometryGroup>

trans-unit.source: Use a CombinedGeometry only when any of the following apply: - The geometric operation is not a union.
trans-unit.target: Bruk en CombinedGeometry bare når en av følgende Bruk:-geometrisk operasjonen er ikke en sammenslåing.

trans-unit.source: - Either of the geometries have a <xref:System.Windows.Media.FillRule> value of <xref:System.Windows.Media.FillRule> and the geometries are self-intersecting (i.e. the <xref:System.Windows.Media.FillRule> actually matters).
trans-unit.target: -Enten geometri må en <xref:System.Windows.Media.FillRule>verdien <xref:System.Windows.Media.FillRule>og av geometri selv kryssende (det vil si at det <xref:System.Windows.Media.FillRule>faktisk viktig).</xref:System.Windows.Media.FillRule> </xref:System.Windows.Media.FillRule> </xref:System.Windows.Media.FillRule>

trans-unit.source: - Time is not a concern, but space is (for instance, if the geometry is created once and then cached).
trans-unit.target: -/ Klokkeslettverdier er et problem, men er plass (for eksempel hvis geometri er opprettet én gang, og deretter bufret).

trans-unit.source: Typically, CombinedGeometry produces smaller output than <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry.AddGeometry%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Vanligvis gir CombinedGeometry mindre utdata enn <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry.AddGeometry%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry.AddGeometry%2A>

trans-unit.source: - The resulting geometry will be stroked or used in a path animation and <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry.AddGeometry%2A> does not provide the desired outline.
trans-unit.target: -Resulterende geometri skal streket eller brukes i en bane-animasjon og <xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry.AddGeometry%2A>ikke inneholder den ønskede rammeomrisset.</xref:System.Windows.Media.PathGeometry.AddGeometry%2A>

trans-unit.target: Freezable funksjoner A CombinedGeometry er en type <xref:System.Windows.Freezable>objektet.</xref:System.Windows.Freezable>

trans-unit.source: For information about <xref:System.Windows.Freezable> features, such as freezing and cloning, see the [Freezable Objects Overview](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: For informasjon om <xref:System.Windows.Freezable>Funksjoner, for eksempel fryse og kloning, kan du se den [oversikt over Freezable](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).</xref:System.Windows.Freezable>
